properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 4:06AM CST until January 8 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...A PERIOD OF LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL DEVELOP LATE TONIGHT AND
CONTINUE INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING...

.Colder air flowing over Lake Superior has led to some lake effect
snow over northern Iron County and will impact the this mornings
commute for the Kimball, Montreal, Gile, and Hurley areas. This
cold air and breezy winds will also lead to very cold wind chills
this morning across most of northeast Minnesota with readings of
-25 to -35 degrees.

More snow will develop tonight into Thursday. The highest
accumulation is expected along portions of the North Shore which
may see up to 6 inches.

* WHAT...Lake effect snow. Additional snow accumulations of up
to one inch.

* WHERE...Iron County.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM CST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute. The cold wind
chills as low as 20 below zero could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST THIS MORNING
